def ini_function(mot_lnk,const_spring):                                           # to reinitialize the constants with updated values gets the motor link value and the constant of spring.
  constant_states = list(set(system.get_q(0))-set(variables))
  constants = system.constant_values.copy()
  constants[r]= mot_lnk                                                           # will eventually be used as the new length of link A (where servo is attached). If I change right now it causes singularities **NEEDS FIXING**
  constants[k_virtual]= const_spring                                            # multiplier of the springs being used
  for key in constant_states:
    constants[key] = initialvalues[key] 
  guess = [initialvalues[item] for item in variables]
  result = c.solve_numeric(variables,guess,constants)
  ini = []
  for item in system.get_state_variables():
      if item in variables:
        ini.append(result[item])
      else:
        ini.append(initialvalues[item])
  return ini    
       
ini = ini_function(9,4)

def run(*args):                                                                 # to evaluate the new system states (motor link length, virtual spring constant)
  ini = ini_function(args[0],args[1])                                           # re-initialize with the new value
  constants = system.constant_values.copy()
  constants[r] = args[0]                                                        # add the new value to system constants
  constants[k_virtual] = args[1]
  constants[qb_ini] = ini[1]                                                    # add the new-initial value to system constants
  constants[qa_ini] = ini[0]                                                    # add the new-initial value to system constants
  states=pynamics.integration.integrate_odeint(func1,ini,t,rtol=tolerance,atol=tolerance,args=({'constants':constants},)) #nonlinear solve to identify a valid initial condition every time the design changes
  return states,constants

Motor link Optimization

#Finding change in end effector position

def measure_perf(args):                                                         # to evaluate system performance with the new length
  new_motor_link_value = args[0]
  if new_motor_link_value > 8.9:                                                               # Setting upper bounds of the link magnitude
    return 1000
  if new_motor_link_value <= 1.5:                                                              # Setting lower bounds of the link magnitude
    return 1000
  try:
    states,constant_values = run(args[0],4)                                     # get  the new system states
    output = Output([grasping_force_scalar],system,constant_values)             # new computation values
    y = output.calc(states,t)                                                   # calculate at t
    perf = 1/(T_max/y[-1])                                                        # Tmax = 0.555N-m;
    return perf
  except scipy.linalg.LinAlgError:
    return 1000

def measure_spring_perf(args):                                                  # to evaluate system performance with the new spring constant value
  new_k_value = args[0]
  if new_k_value > 8:                                                           # Setting upper bounds of the spring constant value
    return 1000
  if new_k_value <= 1:                                                        # Setting lower bounds of the  spring constant value
    return 1000
  try:
    states,constant_values = run(9,args[0])                                     # get  the new system states
    output = Output([grasping_force_scalar],system,constant_values)             # new computation values
    y = output.calc(states,t)                                                   # calculate at t
    perf = (T_max/y[-1])                                                        # Tmax = 0.555N-m;
    return perf
  except scipy.linalg.LinAlgError:
    return 1000
